<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3369] Extend jdbcapi.DataSourceReferenceTest to handle data sources with differing property sets</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3369</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;jdbcaip.DataSourceReferenceTest tests the JavaBean properties of the various data sources Derby has, and also recreation using Reference(able) and serialization/deserialization.&lt;br/&gt;
As part of implementing JDBC statement pooling (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3313&quot; title=&quot;JDBC client driver statement cache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3313&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3313&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), a new property must be introduced in some of the data source classes.&lt;br/&gt;
The test must be extended to handle data sources with differing property sets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are a few comments regarding this in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3325&quot; title=&quot;Add &amp;#39;maxStatements&amp;#39; property to ClientConnectionPoolDataSource&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3325&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3325&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
